package settings

// AdaptiveFetchSettings controls the adaptive subtreeData fetch state
// machine used by blockvalidation and subtreevalidation. The state machine
// itself lives in pkg/adaptivefetch; see that package for the full
// transition truth table and bootstrap semantics.
type AdaptiveFetchSettings struct {
	BootstrapMode             string  `key:"adaptive_fetch_bootstrap_mode" desc:"Initial mode for the adaptive subtreeData fetch gate" default:"pessimistic" category:"AdaptiveFetch" usage:"pessimistic | optimistic | auto" type:"string" longdesc:"### Purpose\nControls whether the node bulk-fetches subtreeData files up front or skips that step. This is a bandwidth/performance choice, not a safety switch: fetching subtreeData is only a prewarm. Whatever the mode, full validation still runs and recovers any genuinely-missing transactions from peers on demand, so correctness and data integrity are the same in every mode. The only thing that changes is *when* the data is fetched.\n\n### Cold-start safety (applies to every mode)\nRegardless of this setting, the gate stays pessimistic (always fetch) until the node's blockchain FSM first reaches RUNNING — i.e. until it is fully synced. This guarantees a cold-start IBD, or a restart while well behind the tip, never skips subtreeData at exactly the moment txs are least likely to be local. Only once the node has been RUNNING does the configured mode below take effect. The latch is one-way: after that first RUNNING a transient catch-up burst (CATCHINGBLOCKS) may still use optimistic mode, because the node has already proven it is synced.\n\n### Values (take effect once the node has first reached RUNNING)\n- **pessimistic** (default) - Always bulk-fetch subtreeData before validation. Lowest validation latency; highest steady-state bandwidth. Safe for every deployment, including standalone nodes without a tx distributor.\n- **optimistic** - Once RUNNING, skip the bulk fetch, assuming txs are already local (delivered by propagation). If that assumption is wrong for some txs, validation simply fetches those txs on demand instead — costing bandwidth at validation time, never correctness. Best when a tx distributor reliably delivers every transaction (e.g. dev-scale-1/2 at 1M TPS).\n- **auto** - Once RUNNING, start pessimistic, then switch to optimistic once the warm-up window is satisfied. See the note below on what 'auto' currently measures.\n\n### What auto currently measures (MVP)\nToday the gate records synthetic observations: pessimistic stamps perfect locality, optimistic stamps zero misses. Two consequences until real counts are plumbed through:\n\n- **Pess→Opt is a warm-up timer, not a measurement.** Once armed at the first RUNNING, with default WindowSize=10 auto switches to optimistic after 10 good observations regardless of how local the txs really were. Granularity differs per service: blockvalidation records one observation per block, subtreevalidation one per subtree — so subtreevalidation can satisfy the window inside a single block. On a node with no tx distributor, auto will still flip to optimistic; nothing breaks, but you gain nothing and may pay more in on-demand fetches than bulk prewarming would have cost. Such nodes should stay on pessimistic for best performance.\n- **Opt→Pess does not switch back on its own.** The OptToPessMissThreshold / OptToPessAvgMissThreshold trips need a real miss count this MVP does not yet provide. A node stuck in optimistic that is missing txs keeps validating correctly (fetching on demand); only the mode metric stays on optimistic and under-reports the extra bandwidth. To force bulk-prewarming back on, set bootstrap_mode to pessimistic and restart — a tuning choice, not a recovery step.\n\n### Recommendations\n- **pessimistic** for mainnet / testnet / teratestnet today (this is the default)\n- **optimistic** for dev-scale 1M-TPS clusters where even one subtreeData download is too expensive\n- **auto** on deployments backed by a reliable tx distributor, accepting the warm-up-timer behaviour above"`
	WindowSize                int     `key:"adaptive_fetch_window_size" desc:"Rolling-window size used for mode transitions" default:"10" category:"AdaptiveFetch" usage:"Number of recent observations to average" type:"int"`
	PessToOptHitRateThreshold float64 `key:"adaptive_fetch_pess_to_opt_hit_rate_threshold" desc:"Min avg local-hit rate (0..1) to switch pessimistic → optimistic" default:"0.99" category:"AdaptiveFetch" usage:"0..1" type:"float64"`
	OptToPessMissThreshold    int     `key:"adaptive_fetch_opt_to_pess_miss_threshold" desc:"Absolute missing-tx count in a single block that immediately trips optimistic → pessimistic" default:"100" category:"AdaptiveFetch" usage:"Immediate safety trip" type:"int"`
	OptToPessAvgMissThreshold float64 `key:"adaptive_fetch_opt_to_pess_avg_miss_threshold" desc:"Avg missing-tx count over the window that trips optimistic → pessimistic" default:"10" category:"AdaptiveFetch" usage:"Rolling-average safety trip" type:"float64"`
}
